cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.SD 

This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning algorithms, which are commonly studied in the sub-category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of system combination methods and the improvement of a standard data set also suggest a focus on machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). Additionally, the identification of base noun phrases involves information retrieval and text analysis, which could fall under the sub-categories of information retrieval (cs.IR) and software development (cs.SD).
